
// This Hyperlambda code concatenates the value of the [base] node, a forward slash, and the first node's value from a specified path using [strings.concat]. It retrieves the base value, appends "/", and then appends the value of the first node from the path "@.dp/#/*/\@src/[0,1]". This is useful for constructing a path or URL by combining base and specific node values.
strings.concat
   get-value:x:@.base
   .:/
   get-value:x:"@.dp/#/*/\\@src/[0,1]"
